s cridder <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/25/01 11:01:35 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/face.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well...</span><hr size=1> Some say 11 hours; some say 8 or 9. All I know is that when I did the quest on my server (Solusek Ro), Broodmother spawned mostly every night between 11 pm and 2 am Pacific time. How do I know for sure? Well, every night there was always some player or group of players waiting on her as well, and we were online around the same time. The night I finished the quest, it was a bit after 11:30 pm Pacific. (Again, this is one particular server.)<br>
<br>
My recommendation to you is to invis and go to her room and log off there. Check back when you can, and each time you log on, you might want to ask the zone if anyone knows when the last spawn was, if the quest was done, etc. Or you can sit there and camp her, but that is hella boring. <br>
<br>
Some rumors have indicated that you can trigger her, but I haven't seen anyone trigger her spawn on my server. If someone claimed they could do it, I'd like to watch them do it. So I'm a skeptic about triggering her.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=niilsemprini>Niil Semprini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/28/01 8:13:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 6 pairs of leggings off one Broodmother spawn</span><hr size=1> Odd thing the other day. I had just gotten my control leash when I noticed that the broodmother was still up. I remember hearing someone shout, &quot;Don't kill the named Giants at the Fort&quot; only 20 minutes before, so I figured she was a pet or something by now. <br>
<br>
So I wander over to the giant fort just in time to see the the broodmother attacking the giants. Figuring someone was doing the quest right then, I followed the fleeing giant to the EW zone. No one stopped him and he dissapeared just as he reached the wall to the right of the zone.<br>
<br>
Cursing myself for not snaring Fergul, I waited around 15 minutes just to see what the broodmother would do next. To my surprise, the quest cycled and Fergul took off running again! I waited until he was almost to the dissapearing point, killed him, and got my leggings.<br>
<br>
Then I waited around for 15 minutes, and the quest cycled again! The quest cycled 6 times and Fergul dropped 6 pairs of leggings, which I let people in GD loot. After that the Broodmother never came back to the fort(I dunno what happened to her), much to the dissapointment of many waiting on a pair.<br>
<br>
I reported this as a bug. I dunno what started the Broodmother in this loop of named giant killing. Perhaps the person who attempted it earlier failed, or perhaps they got their pair and took off happily, not knowing the broodmother hadn't become a pet and was wandering the zone in a predetermined loop. I ended up burning my control leash, needing room to work on tailoring skills.<br>
<br>
I suspect the broodmother was keyed to become a pet when Fleeing_Fergul_00 was attacked, but for some reason he never was. Fleeing_Fergul_00 probably despawned, the Broodmother circled and attacked the giants again, Fleeing_Fergul_01 runs for the zone. When Fleeing_Fergul_01 to Fleeing_Fergul_x get killed, the broodmother never becomes a pet because she is keyed to Fleeing_Fergul_00. Just a guess :) Or maybe the Broodmother was never near anything when I started killing Fergul, as there were many people in GD that day.<br>
<br>
So i guess what I'm saying is keep an eye on the broodmother even if someone has already attempted the quest. That is.. Until they read my bug report and fix it.<br>
<br>
