</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umerci00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merci 00</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://homepage.interaccess.com/~twiki/grafx/10x10.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/1/01 11:26:02 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://homepage.interaccess.com/~twiki/grafx/60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broodmother</span><hr size=1> Yes, that's correct.  A lower level version of Fergul is always up inside the fort (unless players are killing him and giants for faction).  When the Broodmother is quested, as she wanders closer to the cave, that green version will despawn and a newer higher level Fergul will pop outside the fort.  That's the one you want to kill.<br>
