<br>
Good luck! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukatlynel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katlynel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 10:06:34 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.asianavenue.com/indiegrrl/faedrake.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broodmother</span><hr size=1> Finally got around to doing this quest and Landaria is correct as to the number of Ferguls.  I already had my blood wolf harness (they will be auctioned sometimes in NFP if you're patient), went into CC and got the acid off the first orc I killed.<br>
<br>
Complete quest spoiler:<br>
1) Blood wolf harness -- I was able to purchase mine, so I can't speak to the difficulty of getting one.<br>
2) Sceptre/Bottle of karsin acid -- the zone to CC is in the orc fort in EW, run around the inner building and there's a clickable orb in a hut behind the inner fort.  Zone in and start killing orcs, they should drop with a single root and epic cast.  I got my acid off the first orc, could take up to a couple hours.<br>
3) Erdaf Restil is in a bar, all you have to do is track him, go in and turn left and follow your tracking.  Give him the bottle of acid or the sceptre off the queen in CC and get a Gem of Persuasion.<br>
4) Follow the icy river out of Thurgadin.  Invis up and follow the river through the shardwurm caves and hit track to see if broodmother is up ... everything in the cave but broodmother will con green at 56, broodmother cons blue.<br>
5) Once you exit caves, along the river, you'll be able to track to Vores the Hunter ... give him the harness and the gem of persuasion and he will give you a Control Harness.<br>
6) If you're heading south out of Thurgadin, broodmother is in the first cave on the left ... just follow the left wall down to her.  Invis down to her, get next to her out of aggro range of the other wurms, take invis off, hand her the harness, REINVIS, and take off running to the giant fort at neg 3000, neg 3000.  You want to beat the broodmother there.<br>
7) If you track as you head to the fort, you'll notice that Fergul and Grakl will be at the top of your tracking, indicating that they've depopped and repopped outside the fort.  Set yourself up just northeast of the fort so that you'll be between Fergul and the EW zone.  This second Fergul will con green to 56.  Target him and wait.<br>
8) When the broodmother gets to the fort, she'll attack Grakl, green Fergul will disappear from your target window, and you'll see a third Fergul that will con blue to 56.  Target him and root him as quickly as possible once he gets out of aggro range of the rest of the giant fort.  He runs as fast as or faster than SoW, which is why it's important to be northeast of the fort and to root as quickly as possible (it might even help to have SoC memmed in case he starts to away from you).<br>
